  "text": "The H 2 O 2 and O 2 consumption of liver and heart mitochondria were measured in parallel in the same samples under similar experimental conditions. This allowed the calculation of the fraction of electrons out of sequence, which reduce O 2 to ROS at the respiratory chain (the percent free radical leak, FRL) instead of reaching cytochrome oxidase to reduce O 2 to water. Since two electrons are needed to reduce 1 mol of O 2 to H 2 O 2 and four electrons are transferred in the reduction of 1 mol of O 2 to water, the percent FRL, according to the method of Sanz [CITATION_1] , was calculated as the rate of H 2 O 2 production divided by twice the rate of O 2 consumption, and the result was multiplied by 100.",
